Some have even suggested that people in the commissioner's office have been winking at one another while they make public pronouncements against steroid use. They would benefit from taking a step back and looking more carefully at the evolution of the steroid problem in baseball. At the time, many anabolic steroids were illegal if purchased without a prescription. Indeed, it was probably around 10 years ago that some people in baseball became aware that anabolic steroids were being used by some players. 